article.description: Phlandrous Fleming Jr. had 19 points and 12 rebounds to lift Charleston Southern to a 71-61 win over Delaware State on Sunday.
article.headline: Charleston Southern tops Delaware St. 71-61
article.story: JOHNSON CITY, Tenn. -- Phlandrous Fleming Jr. had 19 points and 12 rebounds to lift Charleston Southern to a 71-61 win over Delaware State on Sunday. Fleming Jr. hit all 12 of his foul shots. Dontrell Shuler had 18 points and six assists for Charleston Southern (2-5), which broke its five-game losing streak. Travis Anderson added 12 points. Sean Price had six rebounds for the road team. John Crosby had 23 points for the Hornets (0-7), whose season-opening losing streak reached seven games. Myles Carter added 11 points. John Stansbury had six rebounds. The game was part of the Maui on the Mainland Invitational. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
